124
00:05:51,672 --> 00:05:54,680
Perhaps it sounds less odd this way.

125
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:56,966
Martyrdom, Sarah...

126
00:05:56,966 --> 00:05:58,486
Is a medal...

127
00:05:58,486 --> 00:06:00,881
A badge of honour...

128
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:04,413
Make it your crown jewel and you won't grieve. Ever.

129
00:06:04,413 --> 00:06:07,590
On the frontlines, you die once...

130
00:06:07,590 --> 00:06:11,240
On the home front, we die everyday...

131
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:18,054
Being alive, yet not quite, like this... Turns any honour or medal into helplessness... And grief...

132
00:06:18,330 --> 00:06:19,444
Anyway...

133
00:06:19,444 --> 00:06:21,365
I'm glad...

134
00:06:21,365 --> 00:06:22,996
Why?

135
00:06:24,140 --> 00:06:28,892
You didn't reject me for someone else...

136
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:38,280
Who knows...

137
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:42,111
You may not have to worry about this tomorrow!

138
00:06:42,620 --> 00:06:44,146
Cüneyt...

139
