248
00:14:23,490 --> 00:14:25,980
You're not joining the Army!

249
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:32,056
I don't have a choice, Mum...

250
00:14:32,256 --> 00:14:34,377
You lied to me?

251
00:14:34,377 --> 00:14:36,600
You dare lie to me?

252
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:38,086
Mum...

253
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:44,410
You sat the exam, cleared your medical check-up, and you didn't even tell me!

254
00:14:44,590 --> 00:14:46,184
Your Granny knew this...

255
00:14:46,184 --> 00:14:47,367
Your Granny knew this, didn't she?

256
00:14:47,367 --> 00:14:49,195
Your Granny knew this, didn't she?
-Aye...

257
00:14:50,050 --> 00:14:54,274
You're her grandson... But my son!

258
00:14:55,830 --> 00:14:58,690
I've got no one else...

259
00:14:58,690 --> 00:15:01,860
She's got no one else too...

260
00:15:02,050 --> 00:15:04,476
What d'you want?

261
00:15:08,060 --> 00:15:12,043
D'you want me to end up like her one day?

262
00:15:12,043 --> 00:15:13,699
Yeah?

263
00:15:15,181 --> 00:15:18,239
I can give you everything...

264
00:15:18,239 --> 00:15:23,501
I can give you the security you were looking for...

265
00:15:23,780 --> 00:15:26,283
I can't lose my son...

266
00:15:26,283 --> 00:15:29,557
For some security...

267
00:15:30,325 --> 00:15:34,907
I turned that proposal down... Because you promised me...

268
00:15:34,907 --> 00:15:40,552
And -- I will keep it, Mum... I can fix everything, Mum...

269
00:15:40,924 --> 00:15:43,798
In that case, don't join the Army.

270
00:15:43,798 --> 00:15:46,226
I can't live without you, Vishal...

271
00:15:46,226 --> 00:15:47,534
Mum...

272
00:15:47,534 --> 00:15:53,792
Who says I'll end up like Dad? Millions join the Army... Not all of them get killed in action.

273
00:15:53,792 --> 00:15:57,415
The only one who ever mattered was from our family...

274
00:15:57,415 --> 00:15:59,992
The widow he left behind was your Mum...

275
00:15:59,992 --> 00:16:02,337
The orphan... You!

276
00:16:02,337 --> 00:16:06,153
Are you seriously telling me that not everyone ends up like that?

277
00:16:06,153 --> 00:16:09,923
How are you so sure it won't be you?

278
00:16:10,060 --> 00:16:13,255
Please, Mum... Please!

279
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:15,917
Vishal...

280
00:16:16,384 --> 00:16:18,845
I did...

281
00:16:18,845 --> 00:16:21,512
Just as you said...

282
00:16:21,730 --> 00:16:25,112
You've got to listen to me this time!
-No...

283
00:16:25,112 --> 00:16:28,855
I've always done as you said... Always will...

284
00:16:28,855 --> 00:16:31,013
But... This is something...

285
00:16:31,013 --> 00:16:33,739
I've chosen for myself...

286
00:16:36,490 --> 00:16:40,105
If we want to live...

287
00:16:40,105 --> 00:16:42,024
We must live with honour.

288
00:16:42,024 --> 00:16:44,850
And honour...

289
00:16:44,850 --> 00:16:46,908
In this part of the world...

290
00:16:46,908 --> 00:16:48,992
Means power...

291
00:16:49,190 --> 00:16:52,620
Then -- Join the bureaucracy -- The Civil Service or something...

292
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:56,455
I need the power that comes with a uniform!

293
00:16:56,870 --> 00:16:59,886
A uniform that makes lions of men...

294
00:17:00,090 --> 00:17:03,376
That all? Your reason?

295
00:17:03,770 --> 00:17:08,791
Is that all the Army is to you? Seriously?

296
00:17:09,860 --> 00:17:12,690
The only thing Vijay...

297
00:17:12,690 --> 00:17:15,940
And your Grandpa cared about...

298
00:17:15,940 --> 00:17:19,570
When they joined the Army...

299
00:17:19,570 --> 00:17:22,501
Was the nation... They loved it with their lives...

300
00:17:22,501 --> 00:17:25,588
They honoured their vows to the nation in death...

301
00:17:25,588 --> 00:17:28,940
I don't have just one reason.

302
00:17:29,380 --> 00:17:32,579
I've got many more.

303
00:17:40,610 --> 00:17:42,955
No, Vishal! No!

304
00:17:53,580 --> 00:17:55,415
Mum...

305
00:17:55,669 --> 00:17:59,118
Why'd you have to betray me?

306
00:18:06,890 --> 00:18:09,359
I did everything...

307
00:18:09,359 --> 00:18:13,355
For the honour of the family...

308
00:18:14,138 --> 00:18:20,122
How much more blood will it take to satiate this 'honour' of yours?

309
00:18:22,950 --> 00:18:25,199
What d'you want?

310
00:18:25,770 --> 00:18:31,028
D'you want me to go through everything you're going through?

311
00:18:32,230 --> 00:18:34,880
I've lost my husband...

312
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,911
My world...

313
00:18:36,911 --> 00:18:39,043
My life, as I knew it...

314
00:18:39,043 --> 00:18:41,558
Was gone...

315
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:48,253
You want something to happen to Vishal... So I'm gone for good!
-God forbid...

316
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:51,350
Don't say it...

317
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:54,001
What's it matter?

318
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:58,852
If something happened to him... Sunanda won't be able to live without him...

319
00:18:59,967 --> 00:19:04,612
Please... Stop him, Mum... I beg you...

320
00:19:05,860 --> 00:19:07,459
Please...

321
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:09,719
Stop him...

322
00:19:10,704 --> 00:19:14,450
He's not just my son...

323
00:19:14,450 --> 00:19:17,635
He's your grandson too...

324
00:19:17,635 --> 00:19:21,970
He's Vijay's son... Vijay lives on through him...

325
00:19:21,970 --> 00:19:28,765
Please... Stop him... I can't live without Vishal... Please...

326
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:29,851
Please...

327
00:19:29,851 --> 00:19:32,102
Stop him...

328
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:37,912
He's all we've got left... We can't lose him...

329
00:19:42,570 --> 00:19:44,130
Granny!

330
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:46,620
Where's Nawab?

331
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:48,467
Getting the groceries...

332
00:19:48,467 --> 00:19:53,622
He didn't leave anything for me... I'm knackered... And starving!

333
00:19:53,622 --> 00:19:57,305
He made some kebabs... Let me have a look...

334
00:19:57,440 --> 00:20:01,281
Jesus, it's right here, in front of you!

335
00:20:02,020 --> 00:20:04,460
You don't see anything, do you?

336
00:20:04,460 --> 00:20:07,686
Not when I'm hungry...

337
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:17,947
Vishal got into university...

338
00:20:20,460 --> 00:20:22,295
Who told you?

339
00:20:22,295 --> 00:20:27,413
Vishal's Granny. We talked yesterday.

340
00:20:27,990 --> 00:20:29,976
I'll ask him...

341
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:33,020
He didn't even tell me!

342
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:37,477
Hey! Don't forget to send him some sweets!

343
00:20:37,477 --> 00:20:39,949
We'll be even.

344
00:20:48,390 --> 00:20:49,992
Just a sec.

345
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:54,550
Hello?

346
00:20:54,550 --> 00:20:56,906
Way to go, mate.

347
00:20:56,906 --> 00:20:58,626
What is it?

348
00:20:58,796 --> 00:21:00,354
What d'you mean?

349
00:21:00,354 --> 00:21:05,352
You got your result. Got selected. But you didn't even tell me!

350
00:21:05,352 --> 00:21:06,781
Who told you?

351
00:21:06,781 --> 00:21:10,782
Your Granny told my Granny, of course.

352
00:21:13,910 --> 00:21:15,515
What?

353
00:21:18,430 --> 00:21:25,544
Don't take me for a ride. You got into engineering college and you didn't even bother to tell me!

354
00:21:26,312 --> 00:21:29,610
Just found out today...
-You're so mean...

355
00:21:29,610 --> 00:21:35,257
You always come to me for prayers... I'm sure you've told Neha already though.

356
00:21:35,680 --> 00:21:40,607
Jesus, however did you think of her?
-Just did...

357
00:21:40,902 --> 00:21:42,841
I didn't like it...

358
00:21:42,841 --> 00:21:44,996
But I'm not angry.

359
00:21:44,996 --> 00:21:46,550
Congratulations.

360
00:21:46,550 --> 00:21:49,776
You can hack into my computer now.

361
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:54,001
That's the most I can do...

362
00:21:54,001 --> 00:21:56,157
You don't sound too happy...

363
00:21:56,157 --> 00:22:00,234
Didn't you get into the university of your choice?

364
00:22:00,650 --> 00:22:01,992
No...

365
00:22:03,580 --> 00:22:07,102
Well... That explains the silence...

366
00:22:07,102 --> 00:22:08,351
Anyway...

367
00:22:08,351 --> 00:22:15,709
Big deal... Once you're done... Go for a Masters... You're so bright. What've you got to worry about?

368
00:22:16,625 --> 00:22:17,971
Misfortune...

369
00:22:17,971 --> 00:22:22,259
Why are you so upset? Is it that bad? The uni you got into.

370
00:22:22,259 --> 00:22:25,231
Which uni did you get into, by the way?

371
00:22:26,870 --> 00:22:30,218
Forget it... I've compromised...

372
00:22:30,570 --> 00:22:33,751
It's always good, innit? To compromise...

373
00:22:33,940 --> 00:22:37,428
You asking me or telling me?

374
00:22:37,428 --> 00:22:39,485
How 'bout both?

375
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:44,002
Why are you upset if you've compromised?

376
00:22:44,191 --> 00:22:46,973
It's gonna be good for you.

377
00:22:47,310 --> 00:22:49,103
Good for me...

378
00:22:49,379 --> 00:22:51,099
Aye...

379
00:24:08,430 --> 00:24:10,336
Where's Mum?

380
00:24:18,168 --> 00:24:20,431
In her room...

381
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:34,870
She hasn't had anything...

382
00:24:50,990 --> 00:24:53,030
Don't worry... She will...

383
00:25:06,940 --> 00:25:08,454
Hello?

384
00:25:08,454 --> 00:25:11,625
Your new number, is it, Vishal?

385
00:25:11,710 --> 00:25:13,991
I'm his mother...

386
00:25:13,991 --> 00:25:16,384
Oh... Aunt...

387
00:25:16,477 --> 00:25:18,510
Everything alright?

388
00:25:18,510 --> 00:25:20,616
For now...

389
00:25:20,616 --> 00:25:23,274
Can't be so sure about tomorrow...

390
00:25:23,274 --> 00:25:26,960
What d'yo -- Vishal's okay, right?

391
00:25:30,610 --> 00:25:31,732
I...

392
00:25:31,732 --> 00:25:33,999
I need your help...

393
00:25:33,999 --> 00:25:36,240
I'm all ears...

394
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:38,334
I'll do what I can...

395
00:25:39,131 --> 00:25:44,560
Right now, you're the only one who can stop Vishal from joining the Army...

396
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:47,030
Please... Stop him...

397
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:49,210
What? He's joining the Army?

398
00:25:49,210 --> 00:25:53,351
No -- He got into Engineering... Didn't he?

399
00:25:53,570 --> 00:25:57,010
Who told you?
-He and his Granny.

400
00:25:57,010 --> 00:25:59,368
They lied to you.

401
00:25:59,368 --> 00:26:02,750
He's been selected in the Army.

402
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:08,000
